{"lemma":"طُنُبٌ","slug":"طُنُبٌ","root":"ط.ن.ب","root_slug":"ط-ن-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ط-ن-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":10},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27160"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B7%D9%8F%D9%86%D9%8F%D8%A8%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Cordia africana","tags":["Yemen"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rope, line","tags":["archaic"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"artery or tendon","tags":["archaic"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be curved, crooked, hurled","tags":["archaic","obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have long and weak feet","tags":["archaic","obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have a long back (said of a horse)","tags":["archaic","obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bind or tie with a rope","tags":["archaic","obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to stay, to abide in","tags":["archaic","obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be exceedingly diligent, to be overly zealous","tags":["archaic","obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to howl (said of a wolf)","tags":["archaic","obsolete"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Unknown. Maybe extended from طُنّ (ṭunn, “bundle of reeds”), see there for other comparisons, maybe related with طُنُف (ṭunuf), طُنْف (ṭunf), طَنَف (ṭanaf), طَنْف (ṭanf, “overhang of a mountain or a building, cornice, eaves etc.”), which must be judged by the meanings of Ge'ez ጥንፍ (ṭənf, “prominence; cornice; cross-beam, joint between pillars etc.”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27160","headword_ar":"طُنُبٌ","root":"Tnb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O, L, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TunobN","text_ar":"طُنْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tent-rope:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 687:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a rope with which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayomap","text_ar":"خَيْمَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the like are tied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made fast:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a rope of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xibaA='","text_ar":"خِبَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, L, TA) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suraAdiq","text_ar":"سُرَادِق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.] and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a long rope with which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"srAdq","text_ar":"سرادق"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the tent is tied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made fast;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K, TA;) or, as in the M,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which the tent and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"srAdq","text_ar":"سرادق"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are tied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made fast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extending"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the ground and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaraAy^iq","text_ar":"طَرَايِق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TariyqapN","text_ar":"طَرِيقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.]: (TA:) and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"watid","text_ar":"وَتِد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tent-peg"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; thus in the K, and the like is said in the M; those who make"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alwatidu","text_ar":"الوَتِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the K to be conjoined with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"srAdq","text_ar":"سرادق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as though the author meant that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tnb","text_ar":"طنب"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a long rope with which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"srAdq","text_ar":"سرادق"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the tent, and the peg, are tied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made fast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] being in error: (TA: [but in my opinion, this reading which is disallowed in the TA is more probably correct than the other: in the CK, and in my MS. copy of the K, instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlwatidu","text_ar":"وَالوَتِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", we find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aw Alwtd","text_ar":"او الوتد"},{"kind":"text","text":": in a copy of the A,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aw Alwatiru","text_ar":"او الوَتِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", an obvious mistranscription:]) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTonaAbN","text_ar":"اَطْنَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TinabapN","text_ar":"طِنَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and some of the lexicologists assert that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TunubN","text_ar":"طُنُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as a sing. like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EunuqN","text_ar":"عُنُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and as a pl. like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kutubN","text_ar":"كُتُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (MF, TA;) and Ibn-es-Sarráj says, in one place of his book, that it has no other pl. than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTonaAbN","text_ar":"اَطْنَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but in another place he says that it has this pl. accord. to those who give it a pl., thus giving to understand that there is a difference of opinion as to the plural's being allowable, and that it is used in one form as sing. and pl., which is the case: (Msb, TA:) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTonaAb","text_ar":"اَطْنَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"are the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awaAxiY~","text_ar":"اَوَاخِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=xiy~apN","text_ar":"ا=خِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long ropes of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axobiyap","text_ar":"اَخْبِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xibaA='","text_ar":"خِبَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; the short ropes being called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uSurN","text_ar":"اُصُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", sing."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iSaArN","text_ar":"اـِصَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": the former are the ropes with which the tent is tied, or made fast, between the ground and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaraAy^iq","text_ar":"طَرَايِق"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) As an instance of a tropical usage, (A, TA,) it is related that when El-Ash'ath contracted marriage with a woman, (A, Nh, O, Msb, L,) namely, Meleekeh Bint-Zurárah, (Nh, Msb, L,) on the terms upon which she should decide, (A, Nh, O, &c.,) and she decided upon a hundred thousand dirhems, (A, Nh, Msb, L,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~ahaA Eumaru A_ilaY A^aTonaAbi","text_ar":"رَدَّهَا عُمَرُ اـِلَى اَطْنَابِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayotihaA","text_ar":"بَيْتِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"' Omar reduced her to the dowry of the like of her among the women of her family;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Nh, O, Msb, L;) [lit.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the ropes of her tent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the tent-ropes of her family;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] i. e., to the ground whereon was built the condition of her family, and over which their tent-ropes extended. (Nh, L.) And another tropical usage occurs in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA bayona TunubaYi Almadiynapi A^aHowaju","text_ar":"مَا بَيْنَ طُنُبَىِ المَدِينَةِ اَحْوَجُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"min~iY A_ilayohaA","text_ar":"مِنِّى اـِلَيْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) a saying ascribed to the Prophet, (O,) meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is between the two extremities,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two sides,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the city is more in need of it than I."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sinew,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tendon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ligament,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A,) of the body, (S, M, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that ties the joints and bones:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTonaAbN","text_ar":"اَطْنَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, A.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTonaAbu AlA^aSaAbiEi","text_ar":"اَطْنَابُ الاَصَابِعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The tendons of the fingers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the interossei,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the outer side of the hand, extended above the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sulaAmaY","text_ar":"سُلَامَى"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the wrist to the lowest parts of the fingers."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, * and TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ojaEu","text_ar":"اَشْجَعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.) ―         -b3-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain tendon in the uppermost part of the chest:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) [or,] accord. to the L, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TunubataAni","text_ar":"طُنُبَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TunubaAni","text_ar":"طُنُبَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"?] are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two tendons"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sterno-mastoïdes"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"next the pit of the throat, that extend,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stretch, when a man turns his head aside."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  And (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"root"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a tree: (S, A, O, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTonaAbN","text_ar":"اَطْنَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A:) or this (the pl.) signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"minor roots that branch off from the root-stock"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"main body of the root."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqab~aDato A^aTonaAbuhaA","text_ar":"تَقَبَّضَتْ اَطْنَابُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Its roots contracted;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was planted."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTonaAbu Al$~amosi","text_ar":"اَطْنَابُ الشَّمْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The rays,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beams, of the sun, that extend like sinews,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tendons, at the time of its rising."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~ati","text_ar":"مَدَّتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~amosu A^aTonaAbahaA","text_ar":"الشَّمْسُ اَطْنَابَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aimotad~ato A^aTonaAbuhaA","text_ar":"اِمْتَدَّتْ اَطْنَابُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sun extended its beams"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its beams became extended"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the sun rose."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b6-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iTonaAbapN","text_ar":"اـِطْنَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","A","O","L","Msb","K","TA","Nh","M"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}